The feature are wondering about is multiple subplots, one for each of the 5 signals, from one invocation of rqt_plot. Currently the command in the tutorial displays 5 signals on the same plot.

@namniart's post on [this ROS answers thread](http://answers.ros.org/question/157136/subplots-in-rqt_plot/) from August says that there is no direct support for subplots in rqt_plot. However, @dirk-thomas mentioned a workaround for this on [Github](https://github.com/ros-visualization/rqt_common_plugins/issues/86#issuecomment-21653925) by using multiple instances of the plugin.

We should attempt to use that strategy, and we should explicitly mention that rxplot is unavailable in Groovy and later and rqt_plot should be used instead.
